Vice President Biden met with Prime Minister Hashim Thaci of Kosovo to discuss various issues, including the upcoming advisory opinion of the International Court of Justice on Kosovo's declaration of independence. The Vice President expressed full support for an independent, democratic, multi-ethnic Kosovo within European and Euro-Atlantic institutions. He also reiterated the United States' support for Kosovo's sovereignty and territorial integrity. Biden commended Kosovo's government for progress in carrying out essential reforms and integrating minority communities. He also praised Thaci for his commitment to working with neighboring countries, including Serbia, to promote stability and prosperity in the region.